Following the inauguration of the Steering Board (“the Board”) of the Corporate Governance Rating System (CGRS) and its successful inaugural meeting on 12 December 2017; the Board will reconvene on Friday, 19 January 2018 to consider and approve the results of successful Directors and Companies who passed the CGRS certification exercise. According to the press statement made available to Amehnews by Joseph Kadiri, Media Relation Officer, Corporate Communication of The NSE saying The Board will also consider and approve a date for the certification ceremony for the successful Directors and their Companies which has been tentatively scheduled to hold in the second week of February 2018. The list of successful Directors and Companies will be announced as soon as the result is released by the Steering Board. About CBi The Convention on Business Integrity (CBI), a company limited by Guarantee was established in 1997 with the aim of promoting ethical business practices, transparency and fair competition in the private and public sectors. Its mission is to empower people, their transactions, systems and institutions against corruption. About THE NSE The Nigerian Stock Exchange, a company limited by guarantee, services the largest economy in Africa and is championing the development of Africa’s financial markets. The Exchange offers listing and trading services, licensing services, market data solutions, ancillary technology services, and more. The Nigerian Stock Exchange continues to evolve to meet the needs of its valued customers, and to achieve the highest level of competitiveness. It is an open, professional and vibrant exchange, and the Entrepreneurial Growth hub of Africa. The Nigerian Stock Exchange aspires to be Africa’s foremost securities exchange, connecting Nigeria, with the rest of Africa and the world.